  m_Name: Question_15
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: Which level of AI refers to machines that can perform any intellectual
    task that a human can?
  questionId: 14
  answers:
  - General AI
  - Broad AI
  - Narrow AI
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 00000000
  correctMessage: General AI refers to machines that can perform any intellectual
    task that a human can. Unlike Narrow AI, which is limited to specific tasks,
    General AI has the ability to think abstractly, strategize, and use previous
    experiences to come up with new ideas.
  incorrectMessage: Not quite. Consider which level of AI has the ability to go beyond
    specific tasks and approach human-like intelligence, performing any intellectual
    task that a human can, including abstract thinking and creativity.
